beachhedge:r0007.description: To the east lies a run-down street, cheerfully (and paradoxically) named {greenBright Green} and {yellowBright Gold}. To the west lies the water, and you can see {cyan docks} jutting out from the road a little ways south.

beachhedge:r0008.description: Contrary to its name, the northern district of Beachhedge is home to some of the less savory types of people in the city. As you hurry past closed doors and dark alleys, you begin to wonder if you shouldn't turn back.

beachhedge:r0102.title: {yellowBright Market Way}
beachhedge:r0102.description: This road is bustling with activity. Vendors selling everything from jewelry to fish to exotic spices from every corner of Pannotia are hawking their wares all about you. The sights and sounds are almost overwhelming.

Stalls and vendor carts form an unbroken line around the outer edge of the market, creating a vast shopping area for the citizens of Beachhedge.

beachhedge:r0132.title: The {yellow Eastern Road}
beachhedge:r0132.description: The road here follows the eastern wall of Beachhedge. On the other side, you can see rolling fields leading to distant mountains. A number of modest sized houses line the road.

beachhedge:r0133.title: {cyan Harbor Road}
beachhedge:r0133.description: This road stretches from the northern parts of Beachhedge, past the city {blueBright docks}, and all the way to the southern part of the city, where the wealthiest people live. The {cyan ocean} can be seen to the west.

beachhedge:r0139.title: {blue Fountain Road}
beachhedge:r0139.description: Named for the prominent feature in the town square, this road is lined with fresh flowers and a small artificial waterway. It stretches from the town square southward toward the wealthy district.

beachhedge:r0140.title: {greenBright The City Park}
beachhedge:r0140.description: For a moment, you can almost forget the {gray dinginess} of {yellow Beachhedge} as you walk among the {redBright f}{yellowBright l}{greenBright o}{redBright w}{yellowBright e}{greenBright r}{redBright s}. The park is ringed by {green tall trees}, blocking any view of the decrepit city and giving the park a feeling of {cyan tranquility}.

beachhedge:r0161.description: This seems to be the one place in the city where the ratio of {gray undead} to living creatures is in favor of those with a {magenta pulse}. A path leads eastward to a small {greenBright field} where children can be seen {yellowBright playing}.

beachhedge:r0182.title: The Intersection of {cyan Harbor Road} and {greenBright Emerald Way}
beachhedge:r0182.description: This road stretches from the northern parts of Beachhedge, past the city {blueBright docks}, and all the way to the southern part of the city, where the wealthiest people live. The {cyan ocean} can be seen to the west, and the {yellowBright castle} lies to the east.

beachhedge:r0183.title: {greenBright Emerald Way}
beachhedge:r0183.description: It is immediately apparent that you are in the rich part of the city. Large houses sit well back from the street, and high iron gates keep out those the owners deem undesirable. The road is lined with flowering plants of many shapes and sizes.

beachhedge:r0197.title: Where {greenBright Emerald Way} Meets the {yellow Eastern Road}
beachhedge:r0197.description: You can tell you have entered the rich part of the city. Large houses line the street to the west, high iron gates standing erect in front of them. The road to the north appears pleasant, if less well kept than the one to the west.

beachhedge:r0199.title: A {gray Dingy} Path Leading from the City
beachhedge:r0199.description: This dark path does not appear to be kept up very well, in stark contrast to the area you just left behind. It does, however, seem to be well traveled, as there are many sets of footprints leading away from the city and just as many sets returning.

beachhedge:r0201.title: A {gray Dingy}, Well-Trodden {yellow Path}
beachhedge:r0201.description: The path here seems to be well traveled. You come across the occasional undead servant carrying bags of what you can only assume to be garbage, judging by the terrible odor emanating from their cargo.

beachhedge:r0202.title: {yellow The City Dump}
beachhedge:r0202.description: The makeshift path winds through the towering piles of {yellow garbage}, and you can't help but wonder just why you are here. {red Rats} scurry away when you get close, and the only other company you have is the occasional {gray zombie} dumping a bin of {yellow waste} onto one of the piles.

beachhedge:r0204.title: {gray Deep in} {yellow the City Dump}
beachhedge:r0204.description: You feel as though you've forgotten what {cyan fresh air} smells like. This section of the {yellow dump} is easily the most {magenta repulsive} thing you have ever experienced, and you are fairly certain you will be {red sick} if you do not leave soon.
